to the editor those who say there is no simple solution to the lack of linguists for key security jobs in washington front page april 16 should look to esperanto the artificial language was devised to satisfy the need for a global tongue and is much easier to learn than english is it not conceivable that computers could handle the instantaneous translation of every language into one common form of expression the genius of bill gates could be called on to devise a program amenable to computer users beginning in kindergarten joanna c rovelstad hayward wis april 17 2001

